"title": "8282: intolerance",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8282",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Unwillingness to allow or permit something beyond certain levels. God's intolerance should be the model for God's people, but they should avoid becoming wrongly intolerant.</p>\n<h2>God is intolerant of evil</h2>\n<h3>God is pure and cannot tolerate evil</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab1:13\">HAB 1:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num25:3\">NUM 25:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh7:1\">JOS 7:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam6:7\">2SA 6:7</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr13:10\">1CH 13:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:11\">2KI 17:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps5:6\">PSA 5:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:18\">ROM 1:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:27\">REV 21:27</a></p>\n<h3>God demonstrates his intolerance as the last resort</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer44:22\">JER 44:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod4:10-Exod4:14\">EXO 4:10–4:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:6-Exod34:7\">EXO 34:6–34:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num14:18\">NUM 14:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:30\">NEH 9:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:30\">ACT 17:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:3-Rom2:5\">ROM 2:3–2:5</a></p>\n<h2>Human intolerance should reflect God's attitudes</h2>\n<h3>Human intolerance of God's enemies</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg5:31\">JDG 5:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:26\">1SA 17:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:9\">PSA 69:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:51\">MAT 26:51</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:47\">MRK 14:47</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:50\">LUK 22:50</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:10\">JHN 18:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:6-Eph5:7\">EPH 5:6–5:7</a></p>\n<h3>Human intolerance of ungodliness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:19-Exod32:20\">EXO 32:19–32:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:13-Deut6:15\">DEU 6:13–6:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:115\">PSA 119:115</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:7\">1TI 4:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:16\">2TI 2:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:5\">2TI 3:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:12\">TIT 2:12</a></p>\n<h3>Human intolerance of error</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:10\">TIT 3:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:11\">ACT 17:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:30-Acts20:31\">ACT 20:30–20:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:11-Gal5:12\">GAL 5:11–5:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:6-Eph5:7\">EPH 5:6–5:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:8\">COL 2:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:9\">HEB 13:9</a></p>\n<h3>Human intolerance of evil and sinfulness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:20\">REV 2:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job28:28\">JOB 28:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps34:14\">PSA 34:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps101:4-Ps101:5\">PSA 101:4–101:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:30\">MAT 5:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:12\">ROM 6:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:9\">ROM 12:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:25\">EPH 4:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess3:6\">2TH 3:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:2\">REV 2:2</a></p>\n<h2>Human intolerance can be misguided</h2>\n<h3>It can be a form of hypocrisy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:41-Luke6:42\">LUK 6:41–6:42</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:29-Matt23:30\">MAT 23:29–23:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:14-Luke13:15\">LUK 13:14–13:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:5-John12:6\">JHN 12:5–12:6</a></p>\n<h3>It can amount to exclusiveness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:13\">MAT 23:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:1\">ACT 15:1</a></p>\n<h3>It can be a form of oppression</h3>\n<p>Intolerance of minority, afflicted or underprivileged groups oftens leads to oppression:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod1:11-Exod1:14\">EXO 1:11–1:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:9\">EXO 23:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov14:31\">PRO 14:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov28:3\">PRO 28:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl5:8\">ECC 5:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:31\">MAT 20:31</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:48\">MRK 10:48</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:39\">LUK 18:39</a></p>\n<h3>It can be harshly condemnatory</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:5\">JHN 8:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num21:4-Num21:5\">NUM 21:4–21:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth3:8\">EST 3:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:34-Matt23:35\">MAT 23:34–23:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:45-John7:51\">JHN 7:45–7:51</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:2\">JHN 16:2</a></p>\n<h3>It can be a form of bigotry</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:19\">JHN 15:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num11:27-Num11:29\">NUM 11:27–11:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg12:5-Judg12:6\">JDG 12:5–12:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:15-Matt21:16\">MAT 21:15–21:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:16\">MAT 23:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:18\">MAT 23:18</a></p>\n<h2>Intolerance is usually a matter of decision</h2>\n<h3>Intolerance leading to a good decision</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:4-Luke18:5\">LUK 18:4–18:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:7-Luke11:8\">LUK 11:7–11:8</a></p>\n<h3>Intolerance leading to a bad decision</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:13-Matt19:14\">MAT 19:13–19:14</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:13-Mark10:14\">MRK 10:13–10:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:15-Luke18:16\">LUK 18:15–18:16</a> <em>The disciples' intolerance is counteracted by Jesus Christ's tolerance.</em></p>",
